---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home">
	<h1>Visualizing Fractions with Tape Diagrams</h1>
	<p class="intro">
		Welcome! This project explores how to perform operations on fractions using tape diagrams (also known as strip diagrams).
		Visual models help build a deep conceptual understanding of what it means to add, subtract, multiply, and divide parts of a whole.
	</p>

	<div class="card-grid">
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Addition</h2>
			<p>Learn how to add fractions by finding a common unit.</p>
			<a href="/addition" class="button">Explore Addition &rarr;</a>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Subtraction</h2>
			<p>Visualize removing parts from a fractional amount.</p>
			<a href="/subtraction" class="button">Explore Subtraction &rarr;</a>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Multiplication</h2>
			<p>Understand multiplication as finding "part of a part".</p>
			<a href="/multiplication" class="button">Explore Multiplication &rarr;</a>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Division</h2>
			<p>See division as finding "how many groups" fit inside.</p>
			<a href="/division" class="button">Explore Division &rarr;</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.intro {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}
	.card-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
		gap: 2rem;
	}
	.card {
		background: white;
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
		transition: transform 0.2s;
	}
	.card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-2px);
		box-shadow: 0 10px 15px -3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
	}
	h2 {
		margin-top: 0;
		color: var(--primary);
	}
</style>
